thread.title: Les Miles 9th highest paid college football coach, newspaper reports
thread.title_full: Les Miles 9th highest paid college football coach, newspaper reports | NOLA.com

author: Jim Kleinpeter, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: Les Miles 9th highest paid college football coach, newspaper reports
text:
LSU coach Les Miles is the ninth-highest paid coach in college football and Nick Saban is still No. 1 in a list published by USA Today.
According to the salary database, Miles makes $4,385,567, making him one of four SEC coaches in the top 10. Saban leads the way at $7,087,481. Texas A&M's Kevin Sumlin is No. 7 at $5,000,000 and Ole Miss coach Hugh Freeze is No. 10 at $4,310,000.
Michigan's Jim Harbaugh is second overall at $7,004,000 and Ohio State's Urban Meyer is third at 5,860,000.
1. Nick Saban, Alabama $7,087,481
2. Jim Harbaugh, Michigan $7,004,000
3. Urban Meyer, Ohio State $5,860,000
4. Bob Stoops, Oklahoma $5,400,000
5. Jimbo Fisher, Florida State $5,150,000
6. Charlie Strong, Texas $5,100,270
7. Kevin Sumlin, Texas A&M $5,000,000
8. James Franklin, Penn State $4,400,000
9. Les Miles, LSU $4,388,721
10. Hugh Freeze, Ole Miss $4,310,000
